{"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/BuildingFinancialReports","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/BuildingRevenueModel","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/FinancialStatementsGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/ScenarioAnalysisGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/FinancialRatiosGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/VisualizationGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/DebtAndFinancingGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/EquityFinancingGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/LeaseAccountingGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/LoanAmortization","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/InvestmentAnalysis","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/OptimizationGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/ForecastingGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/PortfolioOptimizationGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/RealOptionsGuide","doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/RiskAnalyticsGuide"],"anchor":"Tutorials","title":"Tutorials","generated":true}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Create comprehensive financial reports with operational metrics, period summaries, and trend analysis.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"title":"Building Multi-Period Financial Reports","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"BusinessMath provides a complete financial reporting system that combines financial statements, operational metrics, and multi-period analysis. This tutorial demonstrates how to build a quarterly financial report with trend analysis, similar to what you’d see in a Goldman Sachs research report or company earnings presentation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The financial reporting system consists of three main components:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OperationalMetrics"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Track industry-specific business drivers (production volumes, pricing, customer counts, etc.)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FinancialPeriodSummary"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Generate comprehensive “one-pager” financial summaries for a single period"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"MultiPeriodReport","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Aggregate multiple periods for trend analysis and growth rate calculations"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This approach is presentation-agnostic - you provide the data structure, and choose how to display it (SwiftUI views, CLI output, or chart visualizations)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Creating-an-Entity","level":2,"text":"Creating an Entity","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Every financial model starts with an entity representing the company or business unit you’re analyzing:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["import BusinessMath","","let entity = Entity(","    id: \"ACME\",","    primaryType: .ticker,","    name: \"Acme Corporation\"",")"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The entity serves as a consistent identifier across all financial statements and metrics.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Building-Financial-Statements","type":"heading","text":"Building Financial Statements"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Create financial statements for each period you want to analyze. For a quarterly report, you’ll typically create four quarterly income statements and balance sheets."}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Income-Statement-for-Q1","type":"heading","text":"Income Statement for Q1"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let periods = (1...4).map({Period.quarter(year: 2025, quarter: $0)})","","\/\/ Revenue accounts","let revenue = try Account(","\tentity: entity,","\tname: \"Product Revenue\",","\ttype: .revenue,","\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [1_000_000, 1_100_000, 1_200_000, 1_100_000])",")","","\t\/\/ Expense accounts","\tlet cogs = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Cost of Goods Sold\",","\t\ttype: .expense,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [400_000, 450_000, 475_000, 440_000]),","\t\texpenseType: .costOfGoodsSold","\t)","","\tlet opex = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Operating Expenses\",","\t\ttype: .expense,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [300_000, 325_000, 310_000, 330_000]),","\t\texpenseType: .operatingExpense","\t)","","\tlet depreciation = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Depreciation & Amortization\",","\t\ttype: .expense,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [50_000, 55_000, 60_000, 52_000]),","\t\texpenseType: .depreciationAmortization","\t)","","\tlet interest = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Interest Expense\",","\t\ttype: .expense,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [25_000, 25_000, 25_000, 25_000]),","\t\texpenseType: .interestExpense","\t)","","\tlet tax = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Income Tax\",","\t\ttype: .expense,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [47_250, 50_000, 50_250, 50_000]),","\t\texpenseType: .taxExpense","\t)","","\t\/\/ Create income statement","\tlet incomeStatement = try IncomeStatement(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tperiods: periods,","\t\trevenueAccounts: [revenue],","\t\texpenseAccounts: [cogs, opex, depreciation, interest, tax]","\t)","","\t\/\/ Asset accounts","\tlet cash = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Cash & Equivalents\",","\t\ttype: .asset,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [500_000, 520_000, 550_000, 570_000]),","\t\tassetType: .cashAndEquivalents","\t)","","\tlet receivables = try Account(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tname: \"Accounts Receivable\",","\t\ttype: .asset,","\t\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [300_000, 280_000, 260_000, 270_000]),","\t\tassetType: .accountsReceivable","\t)","","let ppe = try Account(","\tentity: entity,","\tname: \"Property, Plant & Equipment\",","\ttype: .asset,","\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [2_000_000, 2_000_000, 2_000_000, 2_000_000]),","\tassetType: .propertyPlantEquipment",")","","\/\/ Liability accounts","let payables = try Account(","\tentity: entity,","\tname: \"Accounts Payable\",","\ttype: .liability,","\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [200_000, 180_000, 160_000, 180_000]),","\tliabilityType: .accountsPayable",")","","let debt = try Account(","\tentity: entity,","\tname: \"Long-Term Debt\",","\ttype: .liability,","\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [1_000_000, 1_000_000, 1_000_000, 1_000_000]),","\tliabilityType: .longTermDebt",")","","\/\/ Equity accounts","let equity = try Account(","\tentity: entity,","\tname: \"Shareholders' Equity\",","\ttype: .equity,","\ttimeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: periods, values: [1_600_000, 1_700_000, 1_800_000, 1_750_000]),","\tequityType: .retainedEarnings",")","","\/\/ Create balance sheet","let balanceSheet = try BalanceSheet(","\tentity: entity,","\tperiods: periods,","\tassetAccounts: [cash, receivables, ppe],","\tliabilityAccounts: [payables, debt],","\tequityAccounts: [equity]",")"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Adding-Operational-Metrics","type":"heading","text":"Adding Operational Metrics"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Operational metrics track the business drivers behind your financial performance. These are industry-specific and highly flexible:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let q1Metrics = OperationalMetrics<Double>(","    entity: entity,","    period: q1,","    metrics: [","        \/\/ SaaS metrics","        \"monthly_recurring_revenue\": 300_000,","        \"customer_count\": 250,","        \"average_revenue_per_user\": 1_200,","        \"customer_acquisition_cost\": 5_000,","        \"churn_rate\": 0.02,","        \"net_revenue_retention\": 1.15,","","        \/\/ Unit economics","        \"gross_margin_per_customer\": 720,","        \"lifetime_value\": 36_000,","        \"ltv_to_cac_ratio\": 7.2","    ]",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For different industries, you’d track different metrics:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"E-commerce:","type":"text"}]}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"units_sold"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"average_order_value"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conversion_rate"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Oil & Gas:","type":"text"}]}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"production_boe_per_day"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"realized_price_per_boe"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"lifting_cost_per_boe"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Manufacturing:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"units_produced"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"capacity_utilization"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cost_per_unit"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-Financial-Period-Summary","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Creating a Financial Period Summary"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"FinancialPeriodSummary","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" combines your income statement, balance sheet, and operational metrics into a comprehensive one-pager:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let q1Summary = try FinancialPeriodSummary(","\tentity: entity,","\tperiod: periods[0],","\tincomeStatement: incomeStatement,","\tbalanceSheet: balanceSheet,","\toperationalMetrics: operationalMetrics[0]",")","","\/\/ Access key metrics","print(\"Q1 2025 Financial Summary\")","print(\"Revenue: $\\(q1Summary.revenue)\")","print(\"EBITDA: $\\(q1Summary.ebitda)\")","print(\"Net Income: $\\(q1Summary.netIncome)\")","print(\"Operating Margin: \\(q1Summary.operatingMargin * 100)%\")","print(\"ROE: \\(q1Summary.roe * 100)%\")","print(\"Debt\/EBITDA: \\(q1Summary.debtToEBITDARatio)x\")","print(\"Current Ratio: \\(q1Summary.currentRatio)x\")"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The period summary automatically calculates:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Margins"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Gross, operating, and net margins"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Profitability"}]},{"type":"text","text":": ROA, ROE"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Leverage","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Debt\/Equity, Debt\/EBITDA, Net Debt\/EBITDA"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Liquidity","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Current ratio, quick ratio, cash ratio"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Credit"}]},{"text":": Interest coverage, debt ratios","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Valuation"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": P\/E, P\/B, P\/S, EV\/EBITDA (when market data provided)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Building-a-Multi-Period-Report","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Building a Multi-Period Report"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you have multiple period summaries, create a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MultiPeriodReport"},{"type":"text","text":" for trend analysis:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Create summaries for all four quarters","let summaries = try periods.indices.map { index in","\ttry FinancialPeriodSummary(","\t\tentity: entity,","\t\tperiod: periods[index],","\t\tincomeStatement: incomeStatement,","\t\tbalanceSheet: balanceSheet,","\t\toperationalMetrics: operationalMetrics[index]","\t)","}","","\/\/ Create multi-period report","let report = try MultiPeriodReport(","    entity: entity,","    periodSummaries: summaries",")","","print(\"Acme Corporation - FY2025 Quarterly Report\")","print(\"Periods: \\(report.periodCount)\")"]},{"anchor":"Analyzing-Growth-Rates","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Analyzing Growth Rates"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calculate period-over-period growth for key metrics:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Revenue growth rates","let revenueGrowth = report.revenueGrowth()","for (index, growth) in revenueGrowth.enumerated() {","    let quarter = index + 2  \/\/ Q2, Q3, Q4 (growth from prior quarter)","    print(\"Q\\(quarter) revenue growth: \\(growth * 100)%\")","}","","\/\/ EBITDA growth","let ebitdaGrowth = report.ebitdaGrowth()","print(\"Average EBITDA growth: \\(mean(ebitdaGrowth) * 100)%\")","","\/\/ Net income growth","let netIncomeGrowth = report.netIncomeGrowth()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Growth rates are calculated as: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(Current - Prior) \/ Prior"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Tracking-Trends","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Tracking Trends"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Analyze how key ratios evolve over time:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Margin trends","let grossMargins = report.grossMarginTrend()","let operatingMargins = report.operatingMarginTrend()","let netMargins = report.netMarginTrend()","","print(\"Margin Expansion Analysis:\")","print(\"Q1 Operating Margin: \\(operatingMargins[0] * 100)%\")","print(\"Q4 Operating Margin: \\(operatingMargins[3] * 100)%\")","let expansion = (operatingMargins[3] - operatingMargins[0]) * 100","print(\"Margin expansion: \\(expansion) bps\")","","\/\/ Leverage trends","let debtToEquity = report.debtToEquityTrend()","let debtToEBITDA = report.debtToEBITDATrend()","","\/\/ Profitability trends","let roeTrend = report.roeTrend()","let roaTrend = report.roaTrend()","","\/\/ Valuation trends (if market data available)","let peRatios = report.peRatioTrend()","let evToEBITDA = report.evToEBITDATrend()"]},{"anchor":"Analyzing-Operational-Metrics","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Analyzing Operational Metrics"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a time series from operational metrics to track business drivers:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let metricsTimeSeries = try OperationalMetricsTimeSeries(","    metrics: operationalMetrics  \/\/ Array of OperationalMetrics for each period",")","","\/\/ Extract specific metric","let mrrSeries = metricsTimeSeries.timeSeries(for: \"monthly_recurring_revenue\")","let customerSeries = metricsTimeSeries.timeSeries(for: \"customer_count\")","","\/\/ Calculate growth rates","let mrrGrowth = metricsTimeSeries.growthRate(metric: \"monthly_recurring_revenue\")","let customerGrowth = metricsTimeSeries.growthRate(metric: \"customer_count\")","","\/\/ Analyze unit economics trends","let revenuePerCustomer = quarters.map { quarter in","    let mrr = mrrSeries![quarter]!","    let customers = customerSeries![quarter]!","    return (mrr * 12) \/ customers  \/\/ Annual revenue per customer","}","","print(\"ARPU Trend:\")","for (index, arpu) in revenuePerCustomer.enumerated() {","    print(\"Q\\(index + 1): $\\(arpu)\")","}"]},{"anchor":"Accessing-Specific-Periods","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Accessing Specific Periods"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Retrieve data for specific periods from the report:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ By index","let q1Data = report[0]","let q4Data = report[3]","","\/\/ By period","let q2 = Period.quarter(year: 2025, quarter: 2)","if let q2Data = report[q2] {","    print(\"Q2 Revenue: $\\(q2Data.revenue)\")","    print(\"Q2 EBITDA: $\\(q2Data.ebitda)\")","}","","\/\/ Annual summary (if provided)","if let annual = report.annualSummary {","    print(\"FY2025 Total Revenue: $\\(annual.revenue)\")","    print(\"FY2025 Net Income: $\\(annual.netIncome)\")","}"]},{"text":"Complete Example","level":2,"anchor":"Complete-Example","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Here’s a complete workflow for building a quarterly financial report:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import BusinessMath","","\/\/ 1. Create entity","let company = Entity(id: \"SHOP\", primaryType: .ticker, name: \"ShopCo\")","","\/\/ 2. Define periods","let quarters = Period.year(2025).quarters()","","\/\/ 3. Create financial statements for each quarter","var incomeStatements: [IncomeStatement<Double>] = []","var balanceSheets: [BalanceSheet<Double>] = []","var operationalMetrics: [OperationalMetrics<Double>] = []","","for (index, quarter) in quarters.enumerated() {","    \/\/ Create income statement (simplified)","    let revenue = try Account(","        entity: company,","        name: \"Revenue\",","        type: .revenue,","        timeSeries: TimeSeries(periods: [quarter], values: [1000 * Double(index + 1)])","    )","    \/\/ ... add all accounts","","    let is = try IncomeStatement(","        entity: company,","        periods: [quarter],","        revenueAccounts: [revenue],","        expenseAccounts: [\/* expenses *\/]","    )","    incomeStatements.append(is)","","    \/\/ Create balance sheet","    \/\/ ... similar pattern","","    \/\/ Create operational metrics","    let metrics = OperationalMetrics<Double>(","        entity: company,","        period: quarter,","        metrics: [","            \"units_sold\": 10_000 * Double(index + 1),","            \"customers\": 500 * Double(index + 1)","        ]","    )","    operationalMetrics.append(metrics)","}","","\/\/ 4. Create period summaries","let summaries = try quarters.indices.map {","    try FinancialPeriodSummary(","        entity: company,","        period: quarters[$0],","        incomeStatement: incomeStatements[$0],","        balanceSheet: balanceSheets[$0],","        operationalMetrics: operationalMetrics[$0]","    )","}","","\/\/ 5. Create multi-period report","let report = try MultiPeriodReport(entity: company, periodSummaries: summaries)","","\/\/ 6. Analyze results","print(\"Revenue Growth: \\(report.revenueGrowth())\")","print(\"Margin Trend: \\(report.operatingMarginTrend())\")","print(\"Leverage Trend: \\(report.debtToEBITDATrend())\")","","\/\/ 7. Export as JSON (Codable support)","let encoder = JSONEncoder()","let jsonData = try encoder.encode(report)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Key Design Principles","level":2,"anchor":"Key-Design-Principles","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The financial reporting system follows these principles:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Presentation-Agnostic"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Provides data structures only, not UI\/formatting"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Type-Safe"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Leverages Swift generics for numeric types"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Industry-Agnostic"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Flexible operational metrics adapt to any business model"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Comprehensive"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Automatically calculates 40+ financial ratios"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Codable"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Full JSON serialization support","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Validated","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Entity matching ensures data consistency"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Best-Practices","level":2,"text":"Best Practices"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Consistent Periods"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Ensure all statements for a given period use the same ","type":"text"},{"code":"Period","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let q1 = Period.quarter(year: 2025, quarter: 1)","\/\/ Use q1 for all Q1 accounts"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Validate Entity Consistency","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": The system automatically validates that all summaries belong to the same entity:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ This will throw MultiPeriodReportError.entityMismatch","let report = try MultiPeriodReport(","    entity: entity1,","    periodSummaries: [summary1ForEntity1, summary2ForEntity2]  \/\/ Error!",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Handle Optional Metrics"}]},{"text":": Some ratios require specific data:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Valuation metrics require market data","if let peRatio = summary.peRatio {","    print(\"P\/E Ratio: \\(peRatio)\")","} else {","    print(\"P\/E Ratio: N\/A (no market data)\")","}","","\/\/ Efficiency ratios require specific accounts","if let inventoryTurnover = summary.inventoryTurnoverRatio {","    print(\"Inventory Turnover: \\(inventoryTurnover)x\")","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Calculate Derived Metrics","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Use operational metrics to calculate unit economics:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let revenuePerCustomer = metrics.derived(","    numerator: \"total_revenue\",","    denominator: \"customer_count\"",")"]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Next-Steps","level":2,"text":"Next Steps"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Explore ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMath\/documentation\/BusinessMath\/FinancialStatementsGuide","isActive":true},{"text":" for detailed financial statement modeling","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Learn about ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.jpurnell.BusinessMa